# Docker build context excludes. Keeps the context lean AND correct.
#
# CRITICAL: node_modules must be excluded. The Dockerfile installs Linux deps in an early layer,
# then `COPY . /usr/src/app` copies the source tree over it. If the host's node_modules rides along
# it clobbers the image's freshly installed deps and `next build` fails with
# "Cannot find module .../node_modules/next/dist/bin/next". node_modules + .next are gitignored, so a
# clean CI checkout never carried them; excluding them here makes a local `docker build` reproduce CI.
#
# NOTE: .env is intentionally NOT ignored. It is committed to the repo and `next build` reads the
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* values from it at build time, so it must stay in the build context.
node_modules
.next
.git
.gitignore
*.log
